    "The number of molecules available for training can be artificially inflated by using multiple different SMILES strings representing the same molecule.",
    "SMILES strings encode atom types and their connectivity into a character string in a non-univocal manner.",
    "b. Conformer-based augmentation.",
    "Threedimensional (3D) molecular conformers can be augmented by using multiple conformations (e.g., with different favorable energies) for training, instead of just the minimum energy conformer.",
